Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: Isabelle Urquhart (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Broadway actress Isabelle Urquhart (pictured) started a fashion trend when she decided to reveal her figure on stage by not wearing petticoats?

entry.title: Jewish tartans (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Jewish tartans have been made for the Jewish community of Scotland?

entry.title: Freddy Huayta (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that to combat water privatization in Bolivia, Freddy Huayta joined a "coordinator" – a loose-knit alliance of organizations united around a single cause?

entry.title: Mir nach, spricht Christus, unser Held (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that "Mir nach, spricht Christus, unser Held" (Follow me, says Christ, our hero) is a Christian hymn in German with a text by Angelus Silesius that uses sayings of Jesus in direct speech?

entry.title: a missile strike (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that shortly after a missile strike on the Russian Black Sea Fleet headquarters, Oleksiy Danilov said that the fleet could be "sliced up like a salami" at a later date?

entry.title: United States Conciliation Service (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the United States Conciliation Service, which was part of the U.S. Department of Labor, came to an end because the writers of the Taft–Hartley Act thought that the service was too partial to labor?

entry.title: Dianne Lee (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Dianne Lee had her name changed from Melody to avoid seeming like a reggae act?

entry.title: an island (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that an island vindicated James Cook?
